Description: Lower body sherd of Corinthian pottery globular aryballos; exterior: only faint traces of two sets of three painted narrow concentric bands; inscription near base.
Curator's comments: According to C. W. Neeft (personal communication), the aryballos may be by the Kalauria Painter.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.137) (Phase 1)
